&lt;p&gt;The Rio / KMCR tteam will provide a comprehensive support and development service to the Trust Clinical Applications. It will be made up of Transformation and Integration leads, directing the System Analysts and support Analysts through the management of these systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IT Systems Support analysts are responsible for ensuring that the services they support are experienced by patients, service users, the public, and colleagues; as caring, patient focussed efficient and effective through developing, coordinating and overseeing the provision of first class, administration support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is achieved by ensuring that calls between the service desk and end Users are resolved efficiently, effectively and within agreed timescales. Our analysts will work to fully support the patient or service user journey, by managing role access to RIO and KMCR, general access to applications, triage calls and signpost to the relevant Systems team member and run regular data quality reports. Our analysts are expected to be kind and responsive, professional and informative and to contribute to the quality of our services by demonstrating the behaviours detailed in the Trust ‘&lt;strong&gt;CARE&lt;/strong&gt; Values into action Framework’:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful applicants are required to have the qualification level specified in the person specification in order to carry out the job, however, we do welcome applicants from individuals wishing to further their knowledge and skills and to gain this recognised qualification, which we will support. So if you do not have the essential qualification for the role, this may not be an automatic barrier to you being offered an interview. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are successful at interview but do not have the essential qualification for the role, we will employ you as trainee and will support you to gain this qualification. You will develop new skills and knowledge whilst working with an established team, gaining valuable work experience and continuing to get paid. Once you receive the qualification you will automatically move into the position advertised. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;this post is open to internal candidates only&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview will be held on the &lt;strong&gt;23rd November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
